BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA May 28 -- Chairman of the Vietnam Chamber 
of Commerce and Industry Doan Duy Thanh has recently paid a 
working visit to Britain, Italy, Belgium and France. 
  While in West European countries, Chairman Thanh had working 
sessions with senior officials of the European Community (EC), 
Ministries for Foreign Affairs, Ministries of Industry and Trade 
and representatives of hundreds of trade groups and major banks 
of Western Europe. He also discussed with leaders of the 
Chambers of Commerce of the above-said countries on the 
promotion of economic and commercial cooperation with Western 
Europe. 
  During his visit, Chairman Thanh attended a ceremony on the 
establishment of the France-Vietnam Economic Development 
Association. 

